[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":130},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F29\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-gui\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F29\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-gui\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F29\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-gui\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F29\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-gui\u002F":113,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F29\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-gui\u002F":122},"\u002Fdocker\u002F20230129\u002F345996692\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":96,"date":97,"description":98,"extension":99,"lang":100,"meta":101,"navigation":102,"path":103,"readingMinutes":104,"seo":105,"standalone":106,"stem":107,"tags":108,"tldr":110,"updated":97,"url":111,"__hash__":112},"content\u002Fen\u002FDocker\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-gui.md","(10) Step-by-Step Docker — Docker GUI","6384760976",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":89},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,30,37,40,46,49,52,58,61,64,70,73,76,80,83,86],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Let's circle back to something we haven't covered yet — the Docker GUI.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"docker-gui","Docker GUI",[17,25,26],{},"When you install Docker, you actually install the Docker GUI too — we just haven't used it yet. I held off on it because if you jump straight into the GUI without learning the commands, that's not great practice. In real-world dev work, the command line is more common, and being comfortable with commands actually makes the GUI more productive too.",[17,28,29],{},"On Mac, after you launch Docker you'll see the Docker icon in the menu bar. Click it to open the GUI.",[17,31,32],{},[33,34],"img",{"alt":35,"src":36},"Docker GUI menu","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E4%B8%80%E6%AD%A5%E6%AD%A5%E6%8E%8C%E6%8F%A1%E5%9F%BA%E7%A4%8E-Docker\u002FOIrPXW0.png",[17,38,39],{},"Click \"Dashboard\" and you'll see Docker's status.",[17,41,42],{},[33,43],{"alt":44,"src":45},"Docker Dashboard","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E4%B8%80%E6%AD%A5%E6%AD%A5%E6%8E%8C%E6%8F%A1%E5%9F%BA%E7%A4%8E-Docker\u002Fr2PD6Hf.png",[17,47,48],{},"The GUI lets you quickly start, pause, delete containers — and view Images, etc. Honestly a great tool.",[17,50,51],{},"When you click an Image:",[17,53,54],{},[33,55],{"alt":56,"src":57},"Image details","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E4%B8%80%E6%AD%A5%E6%AD%A5%E6%8E%8C%E6%8F%A1%E5%9F%BA%E7%A4%8E-Docker\u002FJkKpNWm.png",[17,59,60],{},"You can see what the Image does — basically the Dockerfile contents.",[17,62,63],{},"You can also drop straight into a Container's interactive terminal from the GUI:",[17,65,66],{},[33,67],{"alt":68,"src":69},"Open in terminal","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fdocker\u002F%E4%B8%80%E6%AD%A5%E6%AD%A5%E6%8E%8C%E6%8F%A1%E5%9F%BA%E7%A4%8E-Docker\u002FfpHaWTF.png",[17,71,72],{},"Very handy.",[17,74,75],{},"So once you're comfortable with the basic commands, consider using the Docker GUI alongside them — it makes dev work faster.",[12,77,79],{"id":78},"installing-docker-on-windows","Installing Docker on Windows",[17,81,82],{},"If you're installing Docker on Windows, watch out for a few things. If you're on Windows Home Edition, you'll need to enable Hyper-V in Windows before Docker installs properly.",[17,84,85],{},"What's Hyper-V? In short, it's a virtualisation technology that lets your machine run multiple OSes at once.",[17,87,88],{},"So Windows devs need to pay attention to that. Mac and Linux don't have this issue.",{"title":90,"searchDepth":91,"depth":91,"links":92},"",2,[93,94,95],{"id":14,"depth":91,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":91,"text":23},{"id":78,"depth":91,"text":79},"Docker","2023-01-29 15:20:19","Let's circle back to something we haven't covered yet — Docker's GUI.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-gui","2",{"title":6,"description":98},false,"en\u002FDocker\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-gui",[96,109,23],"Step-by-Step Docker",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F29\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-gui\u002F","nnJOxvB8S1uPQplExPlus_CP0S5XZgPms-9BF5blvro",{"newer":114,"older":118},{"url":115,"title":116,"date":117},"\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F29\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-table-of-contents\u002F","(11) Step-by-Step Docker — Table of Contents","2023-01-29 15:22:19",{"url":119,"title":120,"date":121},"\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2023\u002F01\u002F29\u002Fstep-by-step-docker-push-to-docker-hub\u002F","(9) Step-by-Step Docker — Pushing Your Image to Docker Hub","2023-01-29 00:15:09",[123,127,129],{"url":124,"title":125,"date":126,"readingMinutes":104},"\u002Fen\u002Fdocker\u002F2024\u002F12\u002F19\u002Fdockerize-vite-vue-project\u002F","How to Dockerize a Vite + Vue Project","2024-12-19 16:36:18",{"url":115,"title":116,"date":117,"readingMinutes":128},"1",{"url":119,"title":120,"date":121,"readingMinutes":104},1784087325050]